<TITLE> Police appeal for remand of boy nabbed with grenade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Naogaon, Apr 12 (bdnews24.com)  The police have appealed for a 3-day remand of Mahbubul Alam Caeser arrested in possession of a grenade on Monday. Police appealed to the Naogaon Chief Judicial Magistrates Court to quiz Caeser, but the court has sent the minor to prison as the hearing did not took place. The 15-year old was arrested on April 11 from Naogaon. Investigation officer of the case said that the police failed to secure any crucial information from Caeser after primary interrogation. He also added that the minor got arrested while carrying the grenade for money. b
